1
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,670
Forgive me.

2
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,500
I can finally notify you...

3
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:06,900
of my brave death.

4
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,370
No!

5
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:23,030
No.

6
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,530
(EPISODE 14)

7
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:45,230
No. No.

8
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,700
No.

9
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:28,200
Meeting you...

10
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:32,400
was the reward of my life.

11
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:35,870
No.

12
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,930
Please.

13
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:47,500
You said you wouldn't let go of my hands.

14
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,500
You promised me.

15
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:58,170
I will come as the rain.

16
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,530
I will come as the first snowfall.

17
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:08,930
I will beg the divinity...

18
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:13,230
to let me do just that.

19
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,400
Don't do this.

20
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,300
Don't go like this.

21
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:25,930
I love you.

22
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:36,530
I love you. I love you.

23
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:40,930
So do I.

24
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,170
I love you.

25
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:00,500
I already did that...

26
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,230
back there.

27
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,400
No.

28
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,570
(PHYSICS OF LOVE, THE GIRL)

29
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:37,070
(LIKE AN APPLE)

30
00:06:38,670 --> 00:06:40,300
(IT WAS FIRST LOVE.)

31
00:06:45,200 --> 00:07:00,630
(IT WAS FIRST LOVE.)

32
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:32,730
Remember.

33
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,700
You must remember.

34
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,630
His name is...

35
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:39,070
Kim Shin.

36
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:42,230
He's tall...

37
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,070
and has a sad smile.

38
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,100
He'll come as rain.

39
00:07:48,530 --> 00:07:50,370
As the first snowfall.

40
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,300
He'll keep his promise.

41
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,500
(HE'LL KEEP HIS PROMISE.)

42
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:56,930
Remember.

43
00:07:58,130 --> 00:07:59,600
You must remember.

44
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,130
You are...

45
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,770
his bride.

46
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:10,300
(YOU ARE HIS BRIDE.)

47
00:09:05,870 --> 00:09:07,800
The almighty said...

48
00:09:09,530 --> 00:09:12,900
You have been erased from the memories...

49
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,370
of all who knew you.

50
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,200
That is for the sake of their peace...

51
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,930
and it is my grace.

52
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,000
He also said...

53
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:28,370
your punishment is over.

54
00:09:29,170 --> 00:09:32,640
That you can forget everything and sleep...

55
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,140
Be at peace.

56
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:36,600
But...

57
00:09:37,470 --> 00:09:39,230
the goblin's eyes...

58
00:09:39,770 --> 00:09:41,900
filled with tears.

59
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:44,700
Now, I see...

60
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:47,830
what choice I make.

61
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:50,530
So this is...

62
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,400
the choice I made.

63
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,870
I wish...

64
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,600
to remain here.

65
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:10,400
I will remain...

66
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,230
and become rain.

67
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,170
I will become the wind.

68
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,900
I will become the first snowfall.

69
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,670
Just that one thing...

70
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:38,270
Just for that one thing.

71
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:43,100
I ask for your permission just for that one thing.

72
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:48,140
It was indeed a foolish choice he made.

73
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:54,370
I was always in your life.

74
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:01,200
However, in this place,

75
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,000
even I am...

76
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,000
not here.

77
00:11:14,770 --> 00:11:18,170
The goblin survived alone like that,

78
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,870
and he got stuck in the place between this life and afterlife,

79
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:23,070
between light and death,

80
00:11:23,070 --> 00:11:25,230
and where even divinity had abandoned.

81
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:29,030
He got stuck for eternity.

82
00:11:29,470 --> 00:11:30,670
Poor goblin.

83
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:32,870
So?

84
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,930
What happened to the goblin?

85
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:36,170
I don't know.

86
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,970
Memories will soon get forgotten,

87
00:11:40,170 --> 00:11:43,170
and only the glorious futility will remain.

88
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:45,570
He will...

89
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,470
keep walking...

90
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:49,830
in that futility.

91
00:11:49,830 --> 00:11:52,070
What will happen to him...

92
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,570
after that endless walk?

93
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:57,400
Where will he arrive at?

94
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,670
That's one sad story.

95
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:07,630
How much is this?

96
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:22,400
(9 YEARS LATER)

97
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,530
Have a sensible...

98
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:33,270
Have a sensible weekend.

99
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:35,070
It's 10 minutes before showtime.

100
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,570
Here's the script, Ms. Ji.

101
00:12:40,570 --> 00:12:41,600
Thanks.

102
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:44,570
(JI EUN TAK, PRODUCER)

103
00:12:52,030 --> 00:12:53,870
Eun Tak, it's raining.

104
00:12:53,870 --> 00:12:55,470
It's getting heavier.

105
00:12:55,570 --> 00:12:57,930
Are we in Southeast Asia or what?

106
00:12:57,930 --> 00:13:01,070
What's up with the weather forecast? They said it was going to be sunny.

107
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:02,330
I know. I didn't bring an umbrella.

108
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:04,830
That's not the problem. What do we do with the opening?

109
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:06,170
What do you mean what do we do?

110
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,930
We can't make the rain stop, so we have to rewrite the opening.

111
00:13:08,930 --> 00:13:10,970
We can keep this opening for another sunny day.

112
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:12,470
The first song is all right.

113
00:13:12,470 --> 00:13:14,970
It's nice to start a gloomy day with a bright song.

114
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:17,730
Just take out the phrases that don't fit the weather and today's issues.

115
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:19,070
I'm rewriting it.

116
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:21,030
Poor me.

117
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:23,030
It's eight minutes before we go on air.

118
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:25,870
(GYEONG MI)

119
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:29,070
Lend me 300 dollars. It's urgent. Reply as soon as possible.

120
00:13:29,670 --> 00:13:31,900
- I'll go choose the songs. - Okay.

121
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:48,000
Who are you?

122
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:57,370
Was I just mistaken?

123
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:00,770
Well.

124
00:15:02,130 --> 00:15:03,800
It was 20 years ago.

125
00:15:14,570 --> 00:15:16,500
Is this Mom's keepsake?

126
00:15:16,570 --> 00:15:18,670
Since when did I have...

127
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,630
this necklace?

128
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,070
"On that dessert,"

129
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,100
"he was so lonely that..."

130
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,400
"he sometimes walked backwards."

131
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:10,770
"He wanted to see the footsteps in front of him."

132
00:16:17,670 --> 00:16:19,400
(ON THAT DESSERT, HE WAS SO LONELY THAT...)

133
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:42,400
How did only this part...

134
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:46,630
get burnt?

135
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,970
Welcome.

136
00:17:09,370 --> 00:17:12,900
You're always beautiful.

137
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:16,370
Give me soju.

138
00:17:18,030 --> 00:17:21,500
Your show today was good. Did the chief yell at you again?

139
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,670
Being good is useless.

140
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:24,730
I'm close to getting fired because we don't have enough commercials.

141
00:17:24,730 --> 00:17:26,800
And we made a big fuss because of the unexpected rain.

142
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:28,130
I'll take half original and half spicy fried chicken.

143
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,670
Half and half, please.

144
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,340
Go get the soju yourself.

145
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:32,840
I'm your customer, you know?

146
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,770
Hey, Class President. Sit there.

147
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:42,170
Until when will you call her the class president?

148
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:44,500
Welcome, Eun Tak already ordered food.

149
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:45,730
Okay.

150
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,530
I want beer.

151
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,770
Did you win the trial?

152
00:17:55,470 --> 00:17:58,100
I wouldn't have been able to leave the office if I didn't.

153
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,030
Do you want to go on a blind date?

154
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:01,370
I don't like lawyers.

155
00:18:01,370 --> 00:18:03,370
It's a chef this time.

156
00:18:03,370 --> 00:18:05,100
He's frequently on cooking shows,

157
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,870
and he looks like a puppy when he smiles.

158
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:07,870
He's cute.

159
00:18:07,870 --> 00:18:08,970
Why would I date someone who's your type?

160
00:18:08,970 --> 00:18:10,870
Why would I date someone who's a fan of your show?

161
00:18:10,870 --> 00:18:14,070
He always puts on your show during lunch time.

162
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:16,530
Am I the only friend you can sell?

163
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,270
Get sold when someone tries to sell you.

164
00:18:23,370 --> 00:18:24,570
Look at me.

165
00:18:24,570 --> 00:18:28,770
It was the easiest thing for me to become someone's first love.

166
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:32,100
Now there's no man asking me out for a cup of coffee.

167
00:18:34,670 --> 00:18:37,370
Yes. Don't be like her.

168
00:18:37,670 --> 00:18:39,670
What do you mean by that?

169
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:42,630
I thought you were the perfect example to help her understanding.

170
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:44,270
Is she your only friend, Eun Tak?

171
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,770
Is this the only place you can come to drink?

172
00:19:03,570 --> 00:19:05,370
It's raining,

173
00:19:05,370 --> 00:19:07,230
and the drink is bitter.

174
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:11,470
And I have two friends who worry about me.

175
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,230
It's a nice day.

176
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:40,470
I heard she's the goblin's bride.

177
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:41,770
Why can't she see us?

178
00:19:41,770 --> 00:19:43,840
She used to be the goblin's bride.

179
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:47,070
She's 29, and the goblin hasn't appeared yet.

180
00:19:48,570 --> 00:19:50,530
So she's almost like a widow.

181
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:53,900
She used to be able to see me before.

182
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:23,030
What's wrong with me?

183
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:27,340
Why am I so sad?

184
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,170
Why do I keep feeling like this?

185
00:22:24,770 --> 00:22:26,400
It's the first snowfall.

186
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:29,700
You're right. It's really early this year.

187
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:32,400
- It's still nice, isn't it? - Yes.

188
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,130
What have I forgotten?

189
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,200
Whom...

190
00:23:26,470 --> 00:23:28,100
have I forgotten?

191
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:59,070
Whose face have I forgotten?

192
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:03,270
What promise have I forgotten...

193
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:10,470
to be in such profound sorrow?

194
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:13,830
Somebody...

195
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:18,300
Anybody, please...

196
00:24:21,030 --> 00:24:22,670
Please save me.

197
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,400
Me?

198
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,330
Yes, you. Was it you?

199
00:25:53,030 --> 00:25:54,970
Don't do this.

200
00:25:55,270 --> 00:25:58,870
Don't do this. Don't go like this.

201
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:04,630
I love you. I love you.

202
00:27:15,070 --> 00:27:16,330
I'm sorry.

203
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:19,400
My mood swings can get severe. I'm sorry.

204
00:27:26,870 --> 00:27:28,270
What am I doing?

205
00:27:31,170 --> 00:27:33,070
Why am I the one apologizing?

206
00:27:37,130 --> 00:27:38,970
What are you doing right now?

207
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:43,000
Why did you hug me? Do you know me? Who are you?

208
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:48,400
I am the one in the contract.

209
00:27:50,030 --> 00:27:51,230
Contract?

210
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,300
Are you an actor?

211
00:27:58,100 --> 00:28:00,770
- The drama department is... - Did your dream come true?

212
00:28:05,330 --> 00:28:06,770
What are you talking about?

213
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,930
I'm proud of you.

214
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:12,530
Sure, thanks.

215
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:15,900
So why did you hug me back there?

216
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:19,370
And why do you keep talking casually to me?

217
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:23,270
You have been erased from the memories...

218
00:28:23,270 --> 00:28:24,600
of all who knew you.

219
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,930
That is for the sake of their peace...

220
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:29,170
and it is my grace.

221
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,200
As long as you're at peace, I'm fine.

222
00:28:35,970 --> 00:28:37,600
That's all I need.

223
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:40,700
Are you acting right now?

224
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,030
The drama department isn't inside this building.

225
00:28:47,230 --> 00:28:49,370
It's the annex in the back.

226
00:29:20,390 --> 00:29:22,090
By the way, how did you get in here...

227
00:29:22,390 --> 00:29:23,860
without an ID?

228
00:29:25,590 --> 00:29:26,920
Because someone called for me.

229
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:53,290
- Deok Hwa. - Go ahead.

230
00:29:53,290 --> 00:29:56,020
I am the president. You are just an assistant manager.

231
00:29:56,020 --> 00:29:57,460
Go back to your position.

232
00:29:57,890 --> 00:29:59,690
I thought I was pretty natural.

233
00:29:59,690 --> 00:30:00,820
Deok Hwa.

234
00:30:03,020 --> 00:30:04,460
You can't be in here.

235
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,060
- We're sorry. - That man...

236
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:09,120
just said my name, didn't he? He said, "Deok Hwa."

237
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,490
- Deok Hwa. - Please leave.

238
00:30:10,490 --> 00:30:11,760
Leave him alone.

239
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:13,990
Let's hear him out.

240
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:21,820
I thought I would never see you again. I am glad to see you.

241
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,620
Please speak from there. Right there.

242
00:30:24,260 --> 00:30:26,320
Who are you? Do you know me?

243
00:30:28,020 --> 00:30:30,790
I was your uncle, your brother...

244
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:31,920
He must be a lunatic.

245
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,290
I am not a lunatic.

246
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:36,060
I'm hungry. Let's go. What should we eat?

247
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:38,760
I made a reservation at a place that you'd like.

248
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:40,820
Deok Hwa.

249
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:53,890
It's so strange.

250
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:56,720
He said he was my uncle.

251
00:30:58,460 --> 00:31:01,890
Uncle's existence is Chunwoo Group's top secret.

252
00:31:01,890 --> 00:31:04,060
Something only Grandpa and I know.

253
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:05,390
One more person found out about it just now.

254
00:31:05,390 --> 00:31:06,460
Who?

255
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:14,060
Is your uncle's name Kim Shin?

256
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,720
Come on, now.

257
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:19,320
He's my uncle. Why would his last name be Kim? It's Yu.

258
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:20,920
Who's Kim Shin?

259
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,060
Just eat.

260
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:25,720
A family secret.

261
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:28,920
Every corporate heir has a sad story like that.

262
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,760
Don't you worry.

263
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,620
How did I work my way up from the bottom?

264
00:31:32,620 --> 00:31:35,320
I had seollongtang for lunch for years now.

265
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,690
I'll eat this and protect my company.

266
00:31:37,690 --> 00:31:39,360
Like a corporate heir.

267
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:44,160
Deok Hwa. It is not "my company",

268
00:31:44,490 --> 00:31:46,620
but all the employees' company.

269
00:31:46,820 --> 00:31:48,460
They are protecting it well,

270
00:31:48,460 --> 00:31:50,120
so don't be too energetic.

271
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:51,690
Lunch time is over.

272
00:31:51,690 --> 00:31:53,120
Thank you for lunch.

273
00:31:53,690 --> 00:31:55,820
But I'm not... I'm still...

274
00:31:59,090 --> 00:32:00,760
Here are the gift sets.

275
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:02,890
- Thank you. - Thank you.

276
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,460
Enjoy.

277
00:32:24,590 --> 00:32:25,820
Excuse me.

278
00:32:27,290 --> 00:32:28,290
Yes?

279
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:32,220
Just a minute.

280
00:33:04,660 --> 00:33:06,490
I had you close to me,

281
00:33:06,490 --> 00:33:09,120
