Because it was cute.

561
00:50:15,720 --> 00:50:16,890
They are.

562
00:50:18,590 --> 00:50:19,760
Not them.

563
00:50:23,890 --> 00:50:25,190
By the way,

564
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:27,990
are you not going to pay back my five dollars?

565
00:50:27,990 --> 00:50:31,290
If I don't, will we meet again? Will you come see me for the money?

566
00:50:33,260 --> 00:50:35,420
I will for what you've done.

567
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:37,560
You do know what I mean, right?

568
00:50:38,660 --> 00:50:39,690
I don't.

569
00:50:39,690 --> 00:50:43,120
I'm saying I'll call the police on you if this happens again.

570
00:50:43,120 --> 00:50:46,490
I'm not sure why we keep running into each other.

571
00:50:47,260 --> 00:50:48,620
Why did you laugh this time?

572
00:50:50,320 --> 00:50:51,920
Because I'm very happy.

573
00:50:52,890 --> 00:50:55,290
Because this is an unbelievable moment.

574
00:50:57,020 --> 00:50:59,020
Because everything is perfect.

575
00:51:02,190 --> 00:51:04,990
What? Would avoiding you be the wisest thing to do?

576
00:51:05,060 --> 00:51:06,390
Which direction are you headed?

577
00:51:06,560 --> 00:51:07,790
You're leaving again.

578
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:12,260
I'll tune in to your show. I'm a big fan.

579
00:51:12,760 --> 00:51:15,660
How did you know that I do radio shows?

580
00:51:15,660 --> 00:51:17,960
You're way too suspicious now.

581
00:51:17,990 --> 00:51:20,220
I thought you were an actor back then. That's not true, is it?

582
00:51:20,220 --> 00:51:22,420
I'm sorry, but what do you do for a living?

583
00:51:24,290 --> 00:51:26,420
I...

584
00:51:29,190 --> 00:51:31,420
There. I work there.

585
00:51:31,590 --> 00:51:34,690
At that furniture company? What do you do there?

586
00:51:38,060 --> 00:51:39,320
I...

587
00:51:39,590 --> 00:51:42,690
I'm at the top of the hierarchy.

588
00:51:43,590 --> 00:51:46,120
- Excuse me. - You were looking at their papers.

589
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:48,220
Hand them over. It's regarding sponsorship, right?

590
00:51:48,220 --> 00:51:51,660
Give them to me. I'll prove that I'm the boss there.

591
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:58,690
An executive usually signs this, but the CEO has asked for a favor.

592
00:52:00,690 --> 00:52:03,320
He's the CEO?

593
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:06,390
Does he work here at the headquarters?

594
00:52:06,420 --> 00:52:08,220
He doesn't come to work.

595
00:52:09,260 --> 00:52:12,590
Then how should I show my gratitude?

596
00:52:12,990 --> 00:52:15,660
Frankly speaking, I don't even know his number.

597
00:52:15,660 --> 00:52:19,160
And he said I should sign these documents?

598
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:20,760
Why is that?

599
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:27,260
Exactly. I wonder why.

600
00:52:27,890 --> 00:52:30,890
Can you give me your contact information? I'll give it to him.

601
00:52:31,090 --> 00:52:32,320
Thank you.

602
00:52:33,820 --> 00:52:35,860
By the way, is his name...

603
00:52:38,220 --> 00:52:39,860
This is strange, isn't it?

604
00:52:40,490 --> 00:52:42,220
It turns out that way when you get involved with him.

605
00:52:43,020 --> 00:52:45,760
His name is Yu Shin Jae.

606
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:48,490
I see. Thank you.

607
00:52:50,060 --> 00:52:53,560
- Ms. Ji. Ms. Ji. - Ms. Ji. Ms. Ji.

608
00:52:53,560 --> 00:52:55,120
- Ms. Ji. - Way to go.

609
00:52:56,160 --> 00:52:58,560
What happened? How did you land the sponsorship?

610
00:52:59,020 --> 00:53:00,260
I don't know.

611
00:53:00,890 --> 00:53:03,790
I feel like I was put under a spell. It feels like a miracle.

612
00:53:04,390 --> 00:53:06,320
There can't be any other explanation to it.

613
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:09,360
Who cares? What's important is that...

614
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:11,320
our show will survive through the reorganization.

615
00:53:12,460 --> 00:53:14,490
- You're the best. - You're the best, Ms. Ji.

616
00:53:15,060 --> 00:53:19,390
With that going for us, let's do our best on this project.

617
00:53:20,660 --> 00:53:21,990
"We will find you who you're looking for."

618
00:53:21,990 --> 00:53:25,660
"We will find you that person you've forgotten over the years."

619
00:53:25,660 --> 00:53:29,220
"We will help you find lost memories and forgotten faces."

620
00:53:29,290 --> 00:53:31,860
"If you send us your story, we'll introduce it on the show..."

621
00:53:31,860 --> 00:53:34,160
"and connect you to the person you're looking for."

622
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:36,020
This is good.

623
00:53:36,490 --> 00:53:39,860
Search the photo album on each of your phones...

624
00:53:39,860 --> 00:53:41,560
and organize the stories until the next meeting.

625
00:53:41,660 --> 00:53:43,890
Sincerity is what we're looking for.

626
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:45,690
I can tell if it's fake.

627
00:53:45,690 --> 00:53:48,990
Yes, she really can. Do try your best.

628
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:50,420
Okay.

629
00:53:51,820 --> 00:53:53,460
Whose call are you waiting for?

630
00:53:55,320 --> 00:53:56,560
He's not calling.

631
00:54:11,690 --> 00:54:13,020
This is a good project.

632
00:54:13,490 --> 00:54:16,260
Maybe I should go on a search for my first love, too.

633
00:54:17,660 --> 00:54:20,290
You should look for that person. Kim Shin.

634
00:54:23,320 --> 00:54:24,720
Should I?

635
00:54:25,960 --> 00:54:29,990
By the way, was that really your handwriting?

636
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:33,920
It was. That's why it's so strange.

637
00:54:35,060 --> 00:54:36,660
It must've been a ghost.

638
00:54:36,990 --> 00:54:39,460
You saw ghosts until you were in high school.

639
00:54:39,920 --> 00:54:44,560
I hadn't been able to for 9 or 10 years.

640
00:54:44,720 --> 00:54:46,360
I'm seeing them again nowadays.

641
00:54:46,890 --> 00:54:49,660
- There's one behind you now! - Gosh!

642
00:54:50,620 --> 00:54:51,720
Can you hand me the napkin?

643
00:54:52,420 --> 00:54:53,890
Gosh, are you serious?

644
00:55:08,060 --> 00:55:11,490
(YOU MUST REMEMBER. YOU ARE HIS BRIDE.)

645
00:55:12,690 --> 00:55:14,720
What on earth are you?

646
00:55:16,190 --> 00:55:18,620
Why am I your bride?

647
00:55:19,420 --> 00:55:22,560
You are his bride.

648
00:55:23,020 --> 00:55:25,220
Who are you?

649
00:55:26,920 --> 00:55:28,020
Uncle Tenant.

650
00:55:30,590 --> 00:55:33,620
This got mailed to a small building I own.

651
00:55:33,890 --> 00:55:35,120
I don't understand.

652
00:55:35,260 --> 00:55:38,560
It's where the chicken place used to be. I couldn't just throw it out.

653
00:55:39,320 --> 00:55:42,660
I have somewhere to go. I don't know when I'll be back.

654
00:55:42,660 --> 00:55:44,420
You can wait for me, right?

655
00:55:47,890 --> 00:55:49,490
You could give it to this person.

656
00:55:49,690 --> 00:55:52,660
Your name is Ji Eun Tak, Uncle?

657
00:55:52,760 --> 00:55:55,660
Why do you have so many names?

658
00:55:56,620 --> 00:55:57,820
You deliver it to her.

659
00:55:58,490 --> 00:56:00,360
What am I supposed to say to her when we meet?

660
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,290
Then I'll go.

661
00:56:02,290 --> 00:56:05,390
Then give it to Sunny and ask her to deliver it.

662
00:56:05,390 --> 00:56:08,460
She's living on a rooftop of where Sunny lives for some reason.

663
00:56:08,460 --> 00:56:10,390
They're neighbours now.

664
00:56:10,390 --> 00:56:13,490
That won't change anything. It'll make me even more suspicious.

665
00:56:13,720 --> 00:56:17,060
I'll do it. I will look the least suspicious. I own the building.

666
00:56:17,220 --> 00:56:18,860
If it'll make things weird,

667
00:56:19,090 --> 00:56:22,390
I think it'll be the best if you go since you haven't met them.

668
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:28,660
I'll do it. The business owner there is really pretty.

669
00:56:28,820 --> 00:56:31,120
I'll go. Hello?

670
00:56:31,320 --> 00:56:32,560
After nine years,

671
00:56:34,090 --> 00:56:35,590
you can finally come up with an excuse.

672
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:42,490
Can't you hear me?

673
00:56:42,890 --> 00:56:45,620
Who am I talking to right now?

674
00:57:12,490 --> 00:57:13,720
Welcome.

675
00:57:17,020 --> 00:57:18,120
Where's the owner?

676
00:57:18,120 --> 00:57:19,760
She won't be here today.

677
00:57:27,790 --> 00:57:30,020
Where's the owner?

678
00:57:30,020 --> 00:57:33,590
She won't be here today, either. What's going on?

679
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:39,220
- Enjoy. - Thank you.

680
00:57:41,220 --> 00:57:43,790
- Where's the owner? - She won't be here today.

681
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:46,920
What's your name if I may ask? Do you want me to call her?

682
00:57:47,090 --> 00:57:48,190
No.

683
00:57:50,090 --> 00:57:52,090
Just give her this.

684
00:57:53,590 --> 00:57:54,590
Okay.

685
00:59:45,290 --> 00:59:46,490
What is this?

686
00:59:46,490 --> 00:59:49,660
I know. What is that?

687
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:52,020
It came to the old store, not even my current store.

688
00:59:52,020 --> 00:59:54,690
Supposedly, that building owner gave it...

689
00:59:54,690 --> 00:59:56,620
to some good-looking guy who brought it.

690
00:59:56,620 --> 00:59:58,960
So I checked my surveillance video.

691
00:59:59,990 --> 01:00:02,360
He's seriously good-looking.

692
01:00:02,920 --> 01:00:04,260
The old store?

693
01:00:04,260 --> 01:00:05,920
Where was that?

694
01:00:05,920 --> 01:00:07,620
That's what's strange.

695
01:00:07,620 --> 01:00:09,420
It's international mail, too.

696
01:00:09,420 --> 01:00:12,090
It's not like you ever came to that location.

697
01:00:12,090 --> 01:00:13,560
It's strange.

698
01:00:13,760 --> 01:00:16,460
He's so good-looking that it's strange.

699
01:00:16,460 --> 01:00:17,560
What could this be?

700
01:00:18,660 --> 01:00:20,490
This is my handwriting.

701
01:00:21,290 --> 01:00:23,190
Hi, Mom.

702
01:00:23,490 --> 01:00:25,460
To my pretty mom,

703
01:00:25,460 --> 01:00:27,190
who's probably always worrying about me.

704
01:00:27,720 --> 01:00:29,360
How's the afterlife?

705
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:31,420
Is it like this world?

706
01:00:31,790 --> 01:00:35,960
I am writing you a letter from Canada.

707
01:00:35,960 --> 01:00:37,760
You'd be so shocked...

708
01:00:37,760 --> 01:00:40,360
if you knew how I got here.

709
01:00:40,360 --> 01:00:42,020
Just by opening one door,

710
01:00:42,020 --> 01:00:44,560
I can enter a paradise like this.

711
01:00:44,860 --> 01:00:46,690
As long as I'm with him.

712
01:00:47,120 --> 01:00:50,060
I finally have someone who asks how I'm doing.

713
01:00:50,360 --> 01:00:53,820
You may worry and feel bad about...

714
01:00:53,820 --> 01:00:56,220
my seeing things that I shouldn't,

715
01:00:56,320 --> 01:00:58,120
but don't.

716
01:00:58,120 --> 01:01:02,220
Because that is what made me special to someone.

717
01:01:02,820 --> 01:01:05,290
I'm doing well, Mom.

718
01:01:05,420 --> 01:01:07,490
And I'll become even better.

719
01:01:07,560 --> 01:01:10,260
I'll live a good life and become happier than anyone.

720
01:01:10,260 --> 01:01:12,160
Let's meet again someday.

721
01:01:12,260 --> 01:01:13,860
I love you, Mom.

722
01:01:13,860 --> 01:01:16,820
From Canada, your daughter, Eun Tak.

723
01:01:18,290 --> 01:01:19,690
From Canada?

724
01:01:23,160 --> 01:01:25,190
I don't even have a passport.

725
01:01:26,720 --> 01:01:28,120
What is this?

726
01:01:33,920 --> 01:01:36,390
This is too scary.

727
01:01:43,290 --> 01:01:44,490
(REMEMBER. HIS NAME IS KIM SHIN.)

728
01:01:49,590 --> 01:01:51,660
Is that man...

729
01:01:53,420 --> 01:01:55,090
Kim Shin?

730
01:02:02,190 --> 01:02:05,160
Just what happened nine years ago?

731
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:10,590
Just what did I forget?

732
01:02:13,820 --> 01:02:16,490
(HIS NAME IS KIM SHIN. HE'S TALL AND HAS A SAD SMILE.)

733
01:02:30,390 --> 01:02:31,560
Hello?

734
01:02:31,660 --> 01:02:32,960
This is Yu Shin Jae.

735
01:02:35,690 --> 01:02:39,160
Hello. Just a minute.

736
01:02:43,190 --> 01:02:44,660
Hello?

737
01:02:49,060 --> 01:02:50,120
Hello?

738
01:02:54,064 --> 01:02:54,864
Hello?

739
01:02:59,888 --> 01:03:00,888
Hello?

740
01:03:03,170 --> 01:03:06,040
Were you waiting for my call?

741
01:03:10,140 --> 01:03:12,040
I've been busy...

742
01:03:12,210 --> 01:03:15,040
so I even forgot that I gave you my number.

743
01:03:15,670 --> 01:03:17,140
I see.

744
01:03:19,640 --> 01:03:24,040
I didn't get to thank you before. Thank you.

745
01:03:24,040 --> 01:03:25,910
Then would you like to take a walk with me?

746
01:03:26,070 --> 01:03:28,740
Where did you say you lived?

747
01:03:29,310 --> 01:03:30,410
Me?

748
01:03:31,310 --> 01:03:35,040
I didn't tell you where I lived.

749
01:03:37,270 --> 01:03:39,670
So where do you live?

750
01:03:43,810 --> 01:03:46,110
I live near Art Platform...

751
01:03:46,540 --> 01:03:48,670
in Incheon.

752
01:03:48,870 --> 01:03:50,710
Where near Art Platform?

753
01:03:50,710 --> 01:03:54,340
My living situation is quite complicated.

754
01:03:54,940 --> 01:03:57,040
Where are you?

755
01:03:57,770 --> 01:03:59,170
I feel like...

756
01:03:59,740 --> 01:04:02,940
I'll be near Art Platform in about half an hour.

757
01:04:06,170 --> 01:04:09,770
Are you asking me out on a date?

758
01:04:13,710 --> 01:04:14,870
Yes.

759
01:04:15,940 --> 01:04:17,540
I've decided...

760
01:04:17,740 --> 01:04:19,740
to date you.

761
01:04:20,340 --> 01:04:22,410
Call me when you're nearby...

762
01:04:22,640 --> 01:04:24,240
about half an hour from now.

763
01:04:54,870 --> 01:04:56,540
I like that scent, too.

764
01:04:59,010 --> 01:05:02,610
I see. This is a scent that women like.

765
01:05:03,010 --> 01:05:04,910
You must know a lot about women's perfume.

766
01:05:06,870 --> 01:05:09,610
Do you not like the fact that I know a lot about women's perfume?

767
01:05:11,540 --> 01:05:13,040
Who am I to judge?

768
01:05:15,570 --> 01:05:18,140
You are the only woman who knows my number.

769
01:05:19,110 --> 01:05:21,040
Really? Why?

770
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:22,440
That's strange.

771
01:05:22,440 --> 01:05:24,040
There's nothing strange about it.

772
01:05:24,910 --> 01:05:26,670
I just got my phone.

773
01:05:26,870 --> 01:05:28,910
I didn't need a phone for a while.

774
01:05:29,470 --> 01:05:31,470
I was somewhere where phones didn't work.

775
01:05:31,470 --> 01:05:32,840
There was just a lot of snow.

776
01:05:38,140 --> 01:05:39,510
Excuse me for a minute.

777
01:05:50,240 --> 01:05:51,740
I keep forgetting.

778
01:05:51,740 --> 01:05:53,740
I have to take it regularly.

779
01:05:54,110 --> 01:05:55,610
What is that for?

780
01:05:57,240 --> 01:05:59,870
It's medicine to heal the soul.

781
01:06:00,670 --> 01:06:02,040
How long has it been?

782
01:06:02,810 --> 01:06:05,340
May I ask why?

783
01:06:08,070 --> 01:06:10,540
To be honest, I don't know...

784
01:06:10,740 --> 01:06:12,410
how it started.

785
01:06:13,070 --> 01:06:14,640
You may run away.

786
01:06:14,770 --> 01:06:17,710
I was being honest so that I could give you a chance to.

787
01:06:18,980 --> 01:06:21,440
I'm the one who's strange, right?

788
01:06:23,140 --> 01:06:25,040
I'll just try to become stranger.

789
01:06:33,740 --> 01:06:35,270
I'm going on vacation.

790
01:06:35,410 --> 01:06:38,640
I'm telling you in advance in case you drop in...

791
01:06:38,740 --> 01:06:40,640
at Art Platform randomly again.

792
01:06:41,670 --> 01:06:42,840
Where are you going?

793
01:06:42,840 --> 01:06:44,010
Abroad.

794
01:06:44,510 --> 01:06:46,270
It's my first time going abroad...

795
01:06:46,270 --> 01:06:47,940
so I'm very nervous.

796
01:06:48,240 --> 01:06:49,740
I'm so lame, aren't I?

797
01:06:51,070 --> 01:06:53,010
You won't be nervous even if it's your first.

798
01:06:53,510 --> 01:06:55,170
It'll be natural...

799
01:06:55,170 --> 01:06:57,140
as if it weren't your first time.

800
01:06:57,670 --> 01:07:00,440
You'll act like you live there so don't worry.

801
01:07:02,010 --> 01:07:05,270
But you don't know me very well.

802
01:07:06,410 --> 01:07:07,570
Trust me.

803
01:07:11,040 --> 01:07:12,640
Here I go.

804
01:07:12,810 --> 01:07:14,940
One, two.

805
01:07:19,240 --> 01:07:20,240
(VACATION REQUEST)

806
01:07:22,040 --> 01:07:24,010
(REQUEST SUBMITTED)

807
01:07:25,740 --> 01:07:28,340
I feel like there's something there...

808
01:07:28,340 --> 01:07:29,710
so I want to go look.

809
01:07:29,710 --> 01:07:31,170
What's there?

810
01:07:31,610 --> 01:07:33,570
I'm going because I don't know.

811
01:07:33,570 --> 01:07:35,840
Sure. If you don't know, you should go and ask.

812
01:07:35,840 --> 01:07:38,340
Go and ask before you get any older.

813
01:07:40,140 --> 01:07:41,240
You know,

814
01:07:41,240 --> 01:07:44,010
it's an international crime to wear a hooded sweatshirt abroad, right?

815
01:07:44,740 --> 01:07:45,740
Okay.

816
01:07:46,840 --> 01:07:50,340
It's your first trip abroad. Let's try to be fashionable.

817
01:07:50,510 --> 01:07:51,640
Okay.

818
01:07:52,640 --> 01:07:53,840
By the way,

819
01:07:54,670 --> 01:07:58,010
you made a lot of money because your business succeeded.

820
01:07:58,110 --> 01:07:59,570
Why haven't you moved?

821
01:07:59,570 --> 01:08:01,170
Didn't you know?

822
01:08:01,170 --> 01:08:03,110
I own this building. I bought it.

823
01:08:03,110 --> 01:08:05,910
How could I not know? You told me 100 times.

824
01:08:06,110 --> 01:08:08,310
I asked why you don't move.

825
01:08:09,570 --> 01:08:11,210
It's too much of a bother.

826
01:08:11,510 --> 01:08:13,740
And I have a new house phobia.

827
01:08:13,840 --> 01:08:15,840
There's no such thing.

828
01:08:16,340 --> 01:08:17,510
There isn't?

829
01:08:18,040 --> 01:08:19,170
The Clementine are good.

830
01:08:19,310 --> 01:08:20,610
They're really sweet.

